{
  "texts": [
    "Earlier work by Tornatore et al. [51], Gray et al.",
    "[22], and Ji et al. [28] appended basic susceptible-infected-recovered (SIR) type models with uncertainty in the disease transmission rate.",
    "Later work on stochastic epidemic models includes analysis and/or numerical study of stochastic PDE models under a variety of different modeling decisions [1,36,42], and study of seasonality of disease emergence in stochastic ODE models [27].",
    "For overviews on more general stochastic modeling of epidemics, see [2,3].",
    "Notably, Pang and Pardoux [44] formulate a stochastic PDE model which is age-stratified, hence implicitly incorporating some heterogeneous behavior.This work lies at the intersection of compartmental models for epidemiology incorporating human behavior à la [8] and those incorporating stochastic effects à la [22,28,51]."
  ]
}